{"id": "d080678ac279ad873360eadcf4844574416d7fa4d8836a7a37328e97c0f4752f", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:0", "text": "Maya Curves"}
{"id": "96201f29eba169d49c0d029c68c3fc039bfc3f3f4a6051da44323208e813067e", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:1", "text": "Maya curves can be tagged to be rendered.  Create curves with one of the curve tools under:"}
{"id": "7ba0fe28d7a3aa27c13fbd5c8f61ff63396e2800fcba7ecd9e3a1cc266a29517", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:2", "text": "Create > Curve Tools"}
{"id": "b17e18eb88b9f3b8ba1d2f2bfdbe0c0eb989319e235ea789aed8b27adc497823", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:3", "text": "In the Attribute Editor be sure and assign a material to your curves:"}
{"id": "b8199f12ecf7e352807c96dc7a4ee199fe2e17adcfc03ff2d67af5ef87a2f733", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:4", "text": "That's it!  You should see the curve in your render."}
{"id": "27652f3ff0adb6a57d646ae76ecd56cf1d5ccff3e749701c01e7f29930cc60f9", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:5", "text": "For hair/fur curves: To use the IGS/Interactive Xgen surface UVs for color/texture, you can reference this in the PxrManifold2D of your color placement as scalpS and scalpT Primvars."}
{"id": "96036870502339f745205239704c4e95e61a3727326ad1095b918012eaea4258", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:6", "text": "Ribbons"}
{"id": "1bda0e7bdbecc52870339de6a4a9d5ccbd0ed01eb91a9b7194c08fe1c34c3a3f", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:7", "text": "By default, RenderMan renders curves as tubes, which is ideal for hair and fur."}
{"id": "3b3064af4abefc00996b436c356dcccefbd17b50aa73c13ca5981ab26c219cb3", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:8", "text": "For flat, ribbon style curves, the curve needs to be supplied with normals. Maya doesn't have this functionality out of the box, so there's a RenderMan-centric way to accomplish this via"}
{"id": "77750f5b4928f134cc966dbdc0593f8eb436c8f9ec48a9dcc7b2a67edf00c494", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:9", "text": "primvars"}
{"id": "91f9fdbff41fec00b2d8e88a94ce470dd3ba2eafc29ead751e339f5e2ddf80b0", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:11", "text": "Select the curve's shape node (select the curve in the outliner and press the down arrow)."}
{"id": "386c31093aa4f651cc424cdba40003cb8a63c046cace4ad809300d40c2876085", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:12", "text": "Add a RenderMan primvar named rmanNN"}
{"id": "ea5d7a5d80cf4426c4e722554c9e2a552d7bd91e3aa2a130575f62ceaec7505f", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:13", "text": "main menu > Modify"}
{"id": "b63c8ba6d108895ec22d0d6c5db63d74e13bd0fa07f5eab49b640c4567559a7f", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:14", "text": "Add Attribute..."}
{"id": "6bf2a02be78820b452cf943cbeb904cf5ec2b39d28efbd260e1547b7c356a41c", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:15", "text": "Long Name = rmanNN"}
{"id": "cd20fd41354ed6fdde27d9ceb07ee0f7f9c61a64bb0260030f35322bb19e019e", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:16", "text": "data Type = Vector"}
{"id": "f2c54aa30b303bce0e6b0e897788c884658729142ffc692f9cbcdac37936024d", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:17", "text": "Change rmanNN in the curve shape node to anything but 0, for example, 1, 0, 0."}
{"id": "b5742196830bb066c7f5922f6311ca37dcd8e757b93807ce1a1996df239bc21f", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:18", "text": "This will supply the curve with a normal and twist the curve."}
{"id": "2c554c2ba7f0ca9a716ccd73f06afc506108ab9c6af4dd7b3293e5e3a5356a53", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:19", "text": "Maya Scene >"}
{"id": "dcce7f320349c9bf6e5f3256a8cb9ac7bb3f263384a048fa2f52e7d1dd7499d9", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:20", "text": "flat_curve.ma.zip"}
{"id": "fdd0940ede3b4157fa6beaeeeef582980312dbeb6a5df439f45e83f1027820d6", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:21", "text": "Primvars"}
{"id": "a15263c5b1068f3b4f6bb394649ed21af0dd61b106d250072b8f3033e9e47528", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:22", "text": "To learn more about RenderMan Primitive Variables in RenderMan for Maya, check out the About Primitive Variables page:"}
{"id": "8d8cd546b58d91c300d3149ef40b8d98d3061dc38f15ea937d2ed785a3f25771", "item_id": "074d0dbd73:23", "text": "Learn More"}
